		{
			title: "Draconic Energy Core"
			x: -1.0d
			y: 5.0d
			shape: "heart"
			subtitle: "Using the world's smallest battery. Left Click for more info"
			description: [
				"Mekanism's Induction Matrix is too small, or just not your thing? Here's an alternative for you. "
				""
				"The Energy Core is a machine added by Draconic Evolution energy storage system. It is the central part of the Energy Core multiblock which can store massive amounts of RF."
				""
				"When fully assembled, RF can be introduced to and extracted from the structure through the use of Energy Pylons. These can be placed anywhere within 16 blocks of the Core, and are activated by placing a block of Glass either above or below the Pylon (depending if it is below or above the Core, respectively), which will turn into a blue orb. Pylons can be toggled between input and output mode by right clicking the orb, and can move 2,147,483,647 RF/t per face."
				""
				"This structure comes in 8 tiers:"
				""
				"- 1: 45,500,000 RF storage"
				"- 2: 273,000,000 RF storage"
				"- 3: 1,640,000,000 RF storage"
				"- 4: 9,880,000,000 RF storage"
				"- 5: 59,300,000,000 RF storage"
				"- 6: 356,000,000,000 RF storage"
				"- 7: 2,140,000,000,000 RF storage"
				"- 8: Near Infinite RF storage"
				""
				"To build this structure, Right Click the Energy Core to open an interface to select an Energy Core tier and press the 'Assemble Core' button. If the required materials are in your inventory, they'll automatically be placed in their correct spot. Each Tier above the 1st one, will require Draconium Blocks. Higher Tiers will also require Redstone Blocks."
				""
				"Energy Core Stabilizers need to be placed at each cardinal point around the Core, vertically or horizontally as long as it's on the same plane, up to 16 blocks away from the Core."
				""
				"Starting with the 5th Tier, you'll need advanced stabilizers, which are just 3x3 walls made out of Energy Core Stabilizers."
				""
				"Advanced Stabilizers Example:"
				""
				"{image:kubejs:textures/draconic_evolution/advanced_energy_stabilizer_unfinished.png width:100 height:100 align:1}"
				""
				"The example above, shows an unfinished Advanced Stabilizer which need one more Core Stabilizer in the middle. When all 9 Core Stabilizers are placed in a 3x3 wall, they should take this shape:"
				""
				"{image:kubejs:textures/draconic_evolution/advanced_energy_stabilier_finished.png width:100 height:100 align:1}"
				""
				"Lastly, here's an example of a Draconic Energy Core with the 5th Tier:"
				""
				"{image:kubejs:textures/draconic_evolution/draconic_energy_core_example.png width:140 height:100 align:1}"
				""
				"Ps: Use the Stabilizers to access the Core's GUI when building Tiers higher then 1."
			]
			dependencies: ["44EF0C161C89510B"]
			id: "529696648A542802"
			tasks: [
