		{
			title: "The Quantum Item Orchestration System"
			x: -1.0d
			y: -1.0d
			shape: "gear"
			subtitle: "2nd ME? Left Click for more info"
			description: [
				"The QIO System can be considered to be the younger and stronger cousing of the ME System. While it provides large amounts of digital storage for your items, it is NOT as versatile as the ME System. However, the advantage of the QIO System is its ability to work without power on an infinite range. Basically, it will act as the biggest backpack you can ever think of."
				""
				"Like the Quantum Entangloporter, the QIO System also works based on frequency. The whole system it's comprised of at least one QIO Drive (to store items), a QIO Drive Array (to hold the QIO Drives), and at least one QIO Dashboard (to access items in the QIO Drive Array). Both the drive and drive array must be set to the same frequency in order to work together."
				""
				"The QIO Drive Array is a blocks that contains QIO Drives and wirelessly transmits their contents to other QIO devices. In order to work, the drive array must be set to a frequency."
				""
				"QIO Drives are inserted into a Drive Array, allowing it to store more items. Each drive has a number of items and item types it can contain. A basic QIO drive can contain 16000 items and 128 item types, similar to AE2's storage disks."
				""
				"The QIO Dashboards allows a user to interface with the contents of a QIO Drive Array. It looks similar to a chest inventory, but it can be searched, sorted, scrolled through, and shows all items of one type as a single stack, even if there are thousands of them. It also has 3 Crafting Greeds available for you to use as you please. It's basically a Crafting Terminal on steroids. In order to access a drive array, the dashboard must be set to the same frequency as the drive array."
			]
			dependencies: ["484F98FECB918BC5"]
			id: "66DB3A299CCD3279"
			tasks: [
				{
					id: "7903FE47E5B61BC4"
					type: "item"
					item: "mekanism:qio_drive_array"
				}
				{
					id: "656F0059BEBB5759"
					type: "item"
					item: "mekanism:qio_dashboard"
				}
			]
			rewards: [{
				id: "1B1630C5FA5F9A25"
				type: "loot"
				table_id: 3966812906621148304L
			}]
		}
